  "title": "Trader",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>We are seeking a Trader to join our fund management team. The successful candidate will be responsible for executing and managing trading strategies with a strong emphasis on commodities and US stocks/futures, while contributing to portfolio performance, risk management, and market insight. </p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Execute discretionary and systematic trading strategies across commodity markets and US stocks/futures to drive portfolio performance</li><li>Manage day-to-day trading activities including order execution, position management, and liquidity optimization to maximize returns and minimize risk</li><li>Collaborate with portfolio managers, analysts, and risk teams to align trading activities with fund objectives and strategic goals</li><li>Implement and monitor robust risk management practices such as position limits, stop-losses, and stress testing to safeguard fund assets</li><li>Evaluate and recommend new trading opportunities, instruments, and market structures to enhance returns and diversify strategies</li><li>Ensure compliance with internal controls, regulatory requirements, and best execution standards to maintain operational integrity</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Hands-on trading experience with derivatives, futures, options, and OTC instruments related to commodities</li><li>Experience working in a Singapore-based fund management environment is preferred but not mandatory</li><li>Five years of manager-level trading experience within a fund management company is preferred but not mandatory</li><li>Ability to work independently while collaborating effectively within a team-oriented environment</li></ul>",
